@startuml CPU_Registers_State
title EmuAVR - CPU Internal State

class CPU {
    General Purpose Registers:
    R0..R31: uint8_t[32]
    
    Special Registers:
    PC: uint16_t (Program Counter)
    SP: uint16_t (Stack Pointer)
    SREG: uint8_t (Status Register)
    
    Control Flags:
    keep_running_: atomic<bool>
}

note right of CPU
  PC is word-addressed (16-bit words)
  SP points to SRAM data space
  SREG contains AVR status flags:
    - C (Carry)
    - Z (Zero)
    - N (Negative)
    - V (Overflow)
    - S (Sign)
    - H (Half Carry)
    - T (Bit Copy)
    - I (Global Interrupt Enable)
end note

@enduml
